.TH "cpuidle_use_deepest_state" 9 "cpuidle_use_deepest_state" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cpuidle_use_deepest_state \- Set/unset governor override mode.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" cpuidle_use_deepest_state
.BI "(u64 latency_limit_ns "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "latency_limit_ns" 12
Idle state exit latency limit (or no override if 0).
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If \fIlatency_limit_ns\fP is nonzero, set the current CPU to use the deepest idle
state with exit latency within \fIlatency_limit_ns\fP (override governors going
forward), or do not override governors if it is zero.
